<section id="n-dimensional-archetypal-analysis" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="n-dimensional-archetypal-analysis">N-dimensional Archetypal Analysis</h2>
<p>Let <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cmathcal%7BX%7D%20%5Cin%20%7B%5Cmathbb%7BR%7D%5EM%7D%5E%7BI_1%20%5Ctimes%20%5Cdots%20%5Ctimes%20I_N%7D"> be a data tensor where <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cmathbf%7Bx%7D_%7Bi_1,%20%5Cdots%20,i_N%7D%20%5Cin%20%5Cmathbb%7BR%7D%5EM"> be its <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?(i_1,%20%5Cdots,%20i_N)">-th entry.</p>
<p>In this scenario, the archetypal tensor <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cmathcal%7BZ%7D%20%5Cin%20%7B%5Cmathbb%7BR%7D%5EM%7D%5E%7BK_1%20%5Ctimes%20%5Cdots%20%5Ctimes%20K_N%7D"> will be defined as convex combinations of the tensor <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cmathcal%7BX%7D">, i.e.&nbsp;<img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cmathcal%7BZ%7D%20=%20%5Cmathcal%7BX%7D%20%5Ctimes_1%20%5Cmathcal%7BB%7D%5E%7B(1)%7D%20%5Ctimes_2%20%5Cdots%20%5Ctimes_N%20%5Cmathcal%7BB%7D%5E%7B(N)%7D"> where <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cmathcal%7BB%7D%5E%7B(n)%7D%20%5Cin%20%5Cmathbb%7BR%7D%5E%7BK_n%20%5Ctimes%20I_n%7D"> for all <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?n=1,%5Cdots,N"> are stochastic matrices. Simultaneously, the tensor <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cmathcal%7BX%7D"> will be approximated by convex combinations of the archetypal tensor <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cmathcal%7BZ%7D">, i.e.&nbsp;<img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cmathcal%7BX%7D%20%5Csimeq%20%5Cmathcal%7BZ%7D%5Ctimes_1%5Cmathcal%7BA%7D%5E%7B(1)%7D%20%5Ctimes_2%20%5Cdots%20%5Ctimes_N%20%5Cmathcal%7BA%7D%5E%7B(N)%7D"> where <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cmathcal%7BA%7D%5E%7B(n)%7D%20%5Cin%20%5Cmathbb%7BR%7D%5E%7BI_n%20%5Ctimes%20K_n%7D"> for all <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?n=1,%5Cdots,N"> are also stochastic matrices.</p>
<p>What has been described above can be expressed as an optimization problem: <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cbegin%7Bequation%7D%0A%20%20%20%20%5Cargmin_%7B%5Cmathcal%7BB%7D%5E%7B(1)%7D,%20%5Cdots,%20%5Cmathcal%7BB%7D%5E%7B(N)%7D,%20%5Cmathcal%7BA%7D%5E%7B(1)%7D,%5Cdots,%20%5Cmathcal%7BB%7D%5E%7B(N)%7D%7D%20%5Cquad%20%5Cell%5Cleft(%5Cmathcal%7BX%7D%20%7C%20(%5Cmathcal%7BX%7D%20%5Ctimes_1%20%5Cmathcal%7BB%7D%5E%7B(1)%7D%20%5Ctimes_2%20%5Cdots%20%5Ctimes_N%20%5Cmathcal%7BB%7D%5E%7B(N)%7D)%5Ctimes_1%5Cmathcal%7BA%7D%5E%7B(1)%7D%20%5Ctimes_2%20%5Cdots%20%5Ctimes_N%20%5Cmathcal%7BA%7D%5E%7B(N)%7D%5Cright)%0A%5Cend%7Bequation%7D"></p>
<p>such that:</p>
<ul>
<li><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cell%5Cleft(%5Cmathcal%7BX%7D%7C%5Ctilde%7B%5Cmathcal%7BX%7D%7D%5Cright)"> should be a loss function.</li>
<li><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Csum_%7Bk=1%7D%5E%7BK_n%7D%20%5Cmathcal%7BA%7D%5E%7B(n)%7D_%7Bki%7D%20=%201"> with <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cmathcal%7BA%7D%5E%7B(n)%7D_%7Bki%7D%20%5Cin%20%5B0,%201%5D"> for each <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?i=1,%5Cdots,%20I_n"> and <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?n=1,%5Cdots,N">.</li>
<li><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Csum_%7Bi=1%7D%5E%7BI_n%7D%20%5Cmathcal%7BB%7D%5E%7B(n)%7D_%7Bik%7D%20=%201"> with <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cmathcal%7BB%7D%5E%7B(n)%7D_%7Bik%7D%20%5Cin%20%5B0,%201%5D"> for each <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?k=1,%5Cdots,%20K_n"> and <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?n=1,%5Cdots,N">.</li>
</ul>
</section>
